    "what_description": "Hymenostephium serratum is a perennial herb that belongs to the family Asteraceae. It has erect stems that grow up to 1 meter in height, with serrated leaves that are linear to lanceolate in shape and measure up to 10 centimeters in length. The plant produces yellow flower heads with both ray and disc florets, which are arranged in a radiate or discoid pattern. The involucre, which is the leafy structure that surrounds the base of the flower head, is made up of 8-12 phyllaries that are linear to lanceolate in shape. Hymenostephium serratum is native to Mexico and Central America, where it grows in a variety of habitats, including forests and grasslands.",
